    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! I\u2019m parting ways with my trusty ride, and honestly, it\u2019s been such a joy to drive. It\u2019s in really solid shape and has been super reliable for me over the years. I\u2019ve made sure to keep up with the maintenance, so it runs smoothly and looks great inside and out. It\u2019s perfect for someone looking for a dependable car that still feels fresh and fun. I'd love for it to go to a good home\u2014come see it for yourself and let's get you behind the wheel!",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 16
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This E46 M3 is a mechanically sorted example of the final high-revving, naturally aspirated M-cars. Powered by the S54 straight-six, it features individual throttle bodies and a recently recalibrated Double VANOS system, ensuring a linear power band up to the 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory limited-slip differential. Crucially, the rear subframe has been reinforced with plates to address floor fatigue, and the suspension has been refreshed with polyurethane bushings for sharpened turn-in response. While the exterior shows minor stone chips consistent with a driver\u2019s car, the internal mechanicals\u2014including recent rod bearing shells and a cooling system overhaul\u2014are track-ready. This is a high-performance chassis tuned for the purist who values mechanical integrity over a garage-queen aesthetic.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 16
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_3",
